    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Interesting. So you're saying the race and the background of the people living there basically dictate the types of crimes that happen? Like, if this same crime happened in a nicer, suburban neighborhood, would the suspect profile be totally different? Why would the detective assume it's someone from those specific groups just because of where it happened?",
